oanalysis; from precarity to postcolonial studies. "The muse does not like being forced to choose between Agit-prop and Mallarmé," Auden writes with characteristic lucidity, and this study elucidates the probity, humor, and technical skill with which his responses to historical reality in the mid-twentieth century illuminate our world today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEnglish poetryy20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and history. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aShoah.  aW. H. Auden.  aanthropology.  acritical theory.  afascism.  ahistory.  aimperialism.  amarriage equality.  apolitics.  apsychoanalysis.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076648640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363393340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503633933423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503633933/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles